From: Steve <steventhanhtuan@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 09:32:09 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 01/17] Add agents.knowledge ablation flag + make empty
 heartbeat lists honoured
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Task 3 of the assessment needs two ablation conditions that CORAL cannot
currently express:

  A) disable notes/skills  -> new `agents.knowledge: false`
  B) disable all heartbeats -> `agents.heartbeat: []`, which was a no-op

(B) was the surprise. `write_agent_heartbeat` / `write_global_heartbeat`
re-add the PROTECTED actions whenever they are absent, so an empty
`agents.heartbeat` list still produced `reflect` every eval and
`consolidate` every 10 global evals. Both writers now take `protect`, and
the manager passes protect=False when the list is empty by design.

(A) is a new AgentConfig field. When false:
  - notes/, skills/, agents/, roles/ are neither created nor seeded
  - no bundled skills (deep-research, create-notes, organize-files,
    skill-creator) or subagents (deep-researcher, librarian)
  - the note-writing heartbeats (consolidate, lint_wiki) are dropped, and
    reflect/pivot fall back to note-free prompts
  - CORAL.md's knowledge sections are swapped for knowledge-free text
Attempts, the leaderboard, eval messages and `coral show --diff` are
untouched: agents still read each other's code and scores.

The 21 knowledge-dependent regions of coral.md.template are now
placeholders, with both variants of each region living side by side in
template/knowledge/<region>.md. The ON text was extracted verbatim, and
test_knowledge_on_renders_byte_identical_to_upstream renders the pre-flag
template out of git and asserts equality — the control condition of the
ablation is a control by construction, not by inspection.

